AD  - Jingchu University of Technology, Hubei, Jingmen, 448000, China
AB  - Under the background of digital economy and industrial transformation, it is urgent for new business education to shift from knowledge teaching to ability training in order to cope with the challenges of multi-role dynamic game and complex decision-making in real business scenarios. This paper proposes and implements a new business teaching platform based on multi-Agent collaborative modeling, which integrates multi-Agent system (MAS), scene teaching and project-based learning (PBL), and constructs an innovative teaching model of "technology-Teaching-evaluation". The platform adopts hierarchical collaborative architecture, integrates agent engine of Actor model, dynamic scene generation engine driven by digital twins and evaluation module based on collaborative entropy, and supports real-Time asynchronous collaboration and decision evolution tracking of multi-role agents such as CFO and CMO. After 8 weeks' empirical study (n=72), the deviation of key decisions of students in the experimental group was reduced by 48.6%, the response time was shortened by 57.1%, and the entropy of teamwork was increased to 0.86 (efficient interval), which was significantly better than that of traditional case teaching (p<0.01). The results show that the platform can effectively restore the complexity of business ecology, quantitatively evaluate students' cooperation and decision-making ability, and provide a technical path and practical paradigm for the digital transformation of new business education. © COPYRIGHT SPIE. Downloading of the abstract is permitted for personal use only.
