AB  - This work presents a multi-user virtual reality (VR) system integrated with a real-Time sensorized digital twin of an internal combustion engine, aimed at enhancing hands-on learning in mechanical engineering education. The virtual environment, developed in Unity and synchronized via IoT technologies (PLC, Node-RED, and Blynk), enables students to interact with a live virtual replica of the engine, visualize key variables such as RPM, temperature, and pressure, and adjust parameters collaboratively in real time. Through experimental validation with undergraduate students, the approach demonstrated increased engagement, improved data interpretation, and reduced operational risk compared to traditional lab methods. Results also showed enhanced collaboration and a better understanding of Industry 4.0 concepts. This solution bridges the gap between theoretical knowledge and industrial practice, offering a scalable model for modern engineering education. © 2025 IEEE.
