AB  - In response to the problem of weak knowledge of electricity and insufficient cross job collaboration ability among non electricity major learners (legal, financial, management positions) in the field of substation, an "AI driven substation maintenance general education course system"is constructed in combination with artificial intelligence technology. Through an improved collaborative filtering algorithm, accurate matching of job position and knowledge is achieved, and an immersive practical scenario is constructed based on digital twin+AI interaction technology. The course effectiveness is dynamically evaluated using a random forest model. Practice has shown that this course has increased the mastery of electricity knowledge among non electricity major learners by 86.8% (89.2% for legal positions, 85.5% for financial positions, and 83.7% for management positions), improved the accuracy of cross position collaborative decision-making by 30%, and shortened decision-making time by 60%. It provides a practical intelligent solution for the cultivation of cross disciplinary talents in the field of substation. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
