AB  - Technology is changing significantly over the period of time. This research provides the roadmap of industry 5.0 for business perspective. Industry 1.0, 2.0, 3.0, and 4.0 have significantly impacted the manufacturing industry. Industry 1.0 focused on mechanical infrastructures, In contrast, Industry 2.0 brought assembly lines and electricity. The goal of Industry 4.0 was to use new technology to increase mass production and productivity. Industry 5.0 combines human expertise with efficient machines, promoting mass personalization and increasing manufacturing efficiency. This paper offers greener solutions and real-time data collaboration. Industry 5.0 focus on to optimize manufacturing through human know-how and efficient machines, incorporating technologies like Cobots, Internet of everything cloud manufacturing, supply chain management, edge computing, digital twins, IoT, blockchain, and 6G networks. This paper discusses research challenges and opportunities for achieving Industry 5.0. This also examines the impact of digital technologies, including artificial intelligence, on society, commercial operations, educational systems, and public administration. The research provide insightful for professional and scholars.  © 2025 IEEE.
