AB  - The combination of cutting-edge digital technologies with virtual reality, augmented reality, and personalized experiences, in the world of metaverse, contains the potential to completely transform the industry of healthcare. This following work helps in investigating how the metaverse can be incorporated into the field of healthcare by looking at how it might help in improving patient care and medical education alongside healthcare administration. The use of VR and AR simulations for immersive training of medical professionals is one of the standard applications with the use of real-time data taken from different wearable devices for remote monitoring and virtual consultations between doctors and patients. Also, the metaverse makes personalized treatment possible by using AI so that data of the patient should be analyzed using digital twins to optimize hospital operations along with interactive 3D models to enhance education of the patient as well as engagement. The workflow of the metaverse should be supported by enabling technologies such as blockchain, cloud computing, 5G connection, and artificial intelligence. The following technologies discussed above guarantee dependable, fast, and secure interactions. To develop a more effective, accessible, and patient-centered healthcare system, the following article emphasizes the revolutionary impact of metaverse on healthcare. © 2025 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
