AB  - The digitization of cultural heritage is revolutionizing preservation and documentation methods. The creation of digital twins enables the accurate documentation, analysis, and reconstruction of historical sites and monuments. This research paper explores the technical pathways for developing interactive digital replicas of heritage, focusing on the Clock Church in Mosul as a case study. By employing various technologies, the study aims to provide a dynamic platform for research, education, and sustainable tourism, highlighting the transformative potential of digital twins in heritage conservation and outlining a roadmap for future innovations in this field. © 2025 Gesellschaft fur Informatik (GI). All rights reserved.
