AD  - School of Artificial Intelligence, Dongguan City University, Dongguan, 523000, China
AB  - In order to improve the energy efficiency of university classrooms’ lighting and control the electricity cost, this paper proposes a method for the collaborative evaluation of energy conservation and cost budget of university classroom lighting systems based on digital twins. The paper creates a virtual model of the lighting system in university classrooms. Four different power consumption control strategies, namely no energy-saving measures, manual operation, PIR sensor control and facial recognition control, are simulated in the system. By comparing key indicators such as energy consumption, energy-saving efficiency, construction cost and payback period of investment, the results show that PIR sensor control has obvious advantages in energy conservation and consumption reduction, as well as ease of implementation. The PIR sensor control strategy is the best choice for the lighting renovation of university classrooms. Face recognition control can achieve the highest energy-saving effect. However, its high cost and complex installation are not very suitable for large-scale promotion. This research provides valuable references for the renovation decisions of the lighting system in colleges and universities, and also offers practical guidance and technical support for the energy-saving construction of smart campuses and green buildings. © 2025 SPIE. All rights reserved.
