AB  - This paper puts forward a reinforcement learning adaptive teaching engine for building equipment digital twins. The engine proposes to utilize building equipment states in real-Time with the help of digital twin technology and optimize teaching approaches and equipment operation with a deep deterministic policy gradient algorithm. The model structure of the engine consists of data acquisition, digital twin simulation, reinforcement learning decision, and teaching feedback modules, creating a closed-loop system of adaptive optimization. The theoretical background covers an introduction to digital twins, reinforcement learning fundamentals, and engine design principles. Model design focuses on algorithm choice and interface methods to enable efficient decision-making. Simulation and data verification confirm the engine performance. 3D surface plots and heat maps visualization enable the illustration of dynamic changes in equipment states and data interrelations, enhancing energy efficiency and teaching precision. The findings verify that the engine remarkably improves intelligent building equipment management and propels the industry toward sustainable development. © 2025 COPYRIGHT SPIE.
