AB  - Engineering education sits at the intersection of innovation, digital transformation, and competency development. Virtual learning formats present new opportunities to integrate dynamic, interactive content, such as Digital Twins (DTs), and innovative collaboration methods, including Extended Reality (XR). Our concept leverages DTs and XR technology to enhance interactive group work in engineering education. In our efforts to make emerging technologies accessible to diverse stakeholders, we are developing a real, walkable, and dynamic apartment. This physical space acts as a living demonstrator, enabling users to engage with cutting-edge technologies, reducing barriers to adoption, and fostering a deeper understanding of their potential and limitations. From the outset, society is actively involved in the scientific process, emphasizing a transdisciplinary approach that addresses collaboration between academia, industry, and the broader community. By connecting technological innovation with real-world applications, this approach bridges the gap between education, industry, and society while promoting meaningful competency development.  © 2025 The Authors.
