AB  - In response to the problems of subject separation and theoretical practice disconnection in network security education, a “four-dimensional linkage” teaching system based on interdisciplinary network security has been constructed. Through knowledge graph technology, multidisciplinary knowledge integration is achieved, and digital twin technology is used to build a practical environment that integrates theory and practice, forming a “theory practice innovation evaluation” linkage mechanism. A comparative experiment was conducted on 60 undergraduate students, with the experimental group using a four-dimensional linkage system and the control group using a traditional mode. Build a knowledge system covering cryptography, network protocols, system security, etc., and develop practical training modules such as attack and defense exercises and system reinforcement. The experimental results showed that the experimental group was significantly better than the control group in terms of knowledge mastery, practical skills, and innovation ability (P<0.001), verifying the effectiveness of the teaching system. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
