AB  - The critical intersection of advanced technology and rural empowerment can enhance health outcomes and community resilience in underserved areas. As rural regions often face limited access to healthcare infrastructure and security resources, the integration of cognitive technologies such as predictive health analytics offers a transformative solution. By leveraging data analytics and remote monitoring tools, these innovations can identify emerging health risks and enable timely interventions. These tools not only strengthen rural healthcare and safety but also foster sustainable development through proactive, data-informed decision-making. Cognitive Security and Predictive Health Monitoring for Rural Development explores security and prediction technologies and their applications in rural healthcare systems. This book explores the challenges and benefits of implementing these technologies in rural areas. Covering topics such as health monitoring, cognitive security, and urban development, this book is an excellent resource for academicians, researchers, healthcare professionals, public health officials, policymakers, and more. Coverage: The many academic areas covered in this publication include, but are not limited to: Artificial Intelligence Cognitive Security Diagnostic Systems Digital Technologies Digital Twin Technology Grid Search Health Monitoring Healthcare Education Human-Computer Interaction Learning Models Machine Learning Algorithms Mental Health Multi-Disease Diagnosis Rural Health Transformation. © 2026 by IGI Global Scientific Publishing. All rights reserved.
