AB  - The concept and implementation of a digital twin for batteries depend on the underlying models and their applications. This chapter explores essential models contributing to a digital twin and examines their role throughout the battery lifecycle, from manufacturing and testing to operation. Digital twin models are categorised into three main types: production twins, cell twins, and system twins, each addressing specific lifecycle stages and operational needs. Their objectives and interactions are analyzed, demonstrating how they can be synchronised to create a comprehensive and integrated digital twin for batteries. © 2026 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.
