AB  - In order to enrich experimental teaching content, optimise experimental teaching methods, enhance student skills, and promote innovation capabilities, the Ministry of Education initiated the development of national virtual experimental teaching centres as early as 2013. In response to this initiative, our institution has invested substantial resources into research on virtual experimental teaching platforms. This paper focuses on the "Industry 4.0"laboratory established by our institution in 2015, introducing the theme of constructing virtual laboratories. By examining the current state of the Industry 4.0 laboratory, this paper analyses the limitations and issues of the laboratory from multiple dimensions and proposes the goals for constructing an "Industry 4.0"virtual laboratory based on 3D digital twin technology. Additionally, it presents six major application scenarios for the construction and demonstrates their feasibility. This paper provides a practical case for the development of virtual experimental platforms in engineering and intelligent manufacturing, contributing to the advancement of educational modernisation. © 2024 IEEE.
