AD  - Laboratoire Poly-Industrie 4.0, Departement de Mathematiques Et Genie Industriel, Polytechnique Montreal, Montreal, QC, Canada
AB  - The increasing reliance on Internet of Things (IoT) systems has highlighted the need for effective strategies to detect data anomalies and address physical malfunctions in real time. This paper proposes a Cognitive Super Digital Twin (CSDT) to detect data anomalies and flag physical problems in IoT systems. The framework augments a standard DT with a synthetic data layer that balances rare events and improves model learning. We validate the method on an environmental-sensing and robot actuation case study, showing higher recall and F1 when training with augmented data, and a practical DT that detects incomplete robot motions. The approach improves resilience while keeping costs low by prioritizing digital experiments before physical changes. © 2025 The Author(s)
