AB  - The digitalization of the energy industry is accompanied by the active development of digital twin technologies - virtual replicas of real objects based on mathematical models and computational algorithms that reproduce their dynamic behavior. The use of digital twins opens up new opportunities for engineering analysis, optimization of operating modes, prediction of technical conditions, and personnel training without risk to equipment.This study presents the process of developing a digital twin of a dual-circuit heat recovery steam generator (HRSG) that is part of the combined-cycle gas turbine unit CCGT-185. The E-293/40.2-14/1.5-560/294 D (PK-85) HRSG manufactured by JSC "ZIO"was used as the prototype. The model was implemented in the SiminTech 64 software environment, and its validity was confirmed by analytical calculations.  © 2025 IEEE.
