AB  - —The article analyzes the impact of Industry 4.0 technologies on the digitalization of metallurgical production of electrical materials. The authors consider industrial Internet of Things (IoT), Big Data, cloud computing, machine learning, digital twins, robotics, and additive technologies to be tools for increasing production efficiency and improving product quality. They analyzed their advantages and disadvantages. They presented a general scheme for applying the Industry 4.0 technology package to optimize the production processes in the metallurgical production of electrical materials. This article will be useful to automation specialists, students, and teachers of technical universities as well as to employees of the metallurgical industry. ©2024 IEEE.
