TI  - Construction and implementation of intelligent management platform for public training base based on digital twin technology
PY  - 2025
T2  - Proceedings of SPIE - The International Society for Optical Engineering
VL  - 13940
C7  - 139400O
DO  - 10.1117/12.3090127
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105025716331?origin=resultslist
AD  - Binzhou Polytechnic, Binzhou, 256600, China
AB  - This paper presents a construction and implementation scheme of intelligent management platform for public training base based on digital twin technology. By integrating advanced technologies such as computer-Aided design (CAD), computeraided engineering (CAE) and edge computation, the platform constructs a digital twin model with virtual-real mapping and real-Time interaction, and realizes the intelligent management of equipment, teaching and resources in the training base. The core modules of the platform include high-precision virtual-real mapping, intelligent management functions and efficient teaching support. In the experimental verification, the platform shows significant advantages in the virtual and real synchronization accuracy, the improvement of management efficiency and the optimization of teaching effect. Specifically, through three-dimensional laser scanning and dynamic parameter mapping, the platform achieves highprecision virtual-real synchronization with the geometric error of the manipulator less than 0.3 mm and the correlation of dynamic parameters reaching 0.96. Through the long short-Term memory network (LSTM) algorithm, the manipulator fault warning accuracy rate is 86.7%, and the average fault response time is reduced by 61% in the efficient management. In the teaching application, the operation normative score of the experimental group is improved by 24.6% compared with the traditional mode, the task completion time is shortened by 28%, and the energy consumption is reduced by 17%. These achievements provide innovative ideas and practical paths for the intelligent transformation of public training bases, and also provide a reference for the application of digital twin technology in the field of vocational education. © COPYRIGHT SPIE. Downloading of the abstract is permitted for personal use only.
