AB  - This paper discusses the challenge of teaching Digital Twins in computing courses focuses on three key dimensions: emerging technological, economic, and cultural factors; trends likely to influence the educational, professional, and sociocultural experiences of students, educators, and society at large; and a forward-looking vision for the future of computing education. To address these dimensions, the paper proposes a set of adaptable course syllabi designed to align with the specific needs, goals, and institutional contexts of diverse academic environments. These proposals aim not only to introduce students to the foundational principles of Digital Twins but also to foster critical engagement with their broader implications for innovation, interdisciplinarity, and ethical practice in computing. © 2025 IEEE.
