AD  - China Software Testing Center (MIIT Software and Integrated Circuit Promotion Center), Beijing, 102206, China
AB  - Artificial intelligence technology is driving the transformation of software testing and project management towards intelligent collaborative models. This study proposes a dual cycle collaborative framework of "cognition and game", which constructs requirements and tests semantic mapping through multimodal large models, and combines reinforcement learning and digital twin technology to achieve dynamic generation of testing scenarios, real-time prediction of defect risks, and optimization of resource scheduling. At the methodological level, the innovative introduction of asymmetric Nash equilibrium algorithm breaks through the multi-objective conflicts of quality, schedule, and cost, improves demand response efficiency, and reduces defect leakage rate. Case studies have shown that this model successfully balanced collaborative testing of 23 micro services in a core system transformation, shortened delivery cycles by 78%, avoided economic losses of millions of Yuan, and verified the deep coupling effect of AI driven testing and management. This study provides a theoretical paradigm and implementation path for the intelligent engineering practice of complex systems. © Conference Proceedings of the 13th International Symposium on Project Management, ISPM 2025.
