AB  - Digital Twin (DT) technology adoption is rapidly accelerating, particularly in cyber-physical systems. However, our research shows that technology has evolved much quicker than educational curricula leaving a big gap between what students learn and the skills the industry desires. This paper is motivated by this need and outlines the ongoing development of a Graduate Certificate in DTs, an innovative educational program currently being developed at the School of Modeling, Simulation, and Training at the University of Central Florida. This program targets students from diverse technical backgrounds, aiming to meet the growing demand for professionals skilled in DT design, implementation, and application. It focuses on core competencies including DT architecture, AI/ML integration, real-time data synchronization, modeling, simulation, and visualization. This paper details the program's envisioned structure, curriculum, courses, teaching strategies, and potential impact on preparing the future workforce for the evolving DT sector. © 2025 Society for Modeling & Simulation International (SCS).
