DO  - 10.1117/12.3087533
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105029497738?origin=resultslist
AD  - Wuhan College of Arts & Sciences, Wuhan, 430000, China
AB  - As an important part of the new generation of information technology, digital twin technology has been widely used in industry, medical care, education and other fields. This paper discusses the application prospects and implementation strategies of digital twin technology in the construction of computer professional courses in private universities. The study first analyzes the challenges faced by the construction of computer professional courses in private universities, including insufficient practical teaching resources, lagging course content updates, and single teaching models. Subsequently, the advantages of digital twin technology in course construction are explained, such as the combination of virtual and real, real-time interaction, and data-driven characteristics. Based on this, the specific implementation path of digital twin technology to empower the construction of computer professional courses in private universities is proposed: building a digital twin model of the course, developing a virtual experimental teaching platform, optimizing course content and teaching methods, and establishing a data-driven teaching evaluation system. Through case analysis, the positive role of digital twin technology in improving teaching quality, enhancing students' practical ability, and promoting continuous optimization of courses is verified. Finally, the challenges and solutions that may be encountered during the implementation process are discussed, providing new ideas and methods for the construction of computer professional courses in private universities. © 2025 The Authors.
