AB  - In this chapter, a user-centered method (considering medical teams and patients) is given for designing a mechanism with a Remote Center of Motion (RCM) for medical robots. First, the need for this particular motion is demonstrated for different medical applications. Next, the important step of describing the necessary specifications for medical robots is developed. The choice of a suitable kinematic structure for the medical application depends on this step. In the following section, kinematic structures of RCMs are thoroughly surveyed, and examples of medical robots are given. This is followed by an optimization section based on two different medical robots, demonstrating the importance of the choice of criteria in the optimization result. The development of digital twins for medical robots reduces study time by involving the medical team throughout the design process. Finally, the different possibilities for creating a RCM are discussed, and new, original kinematic structures are presented. © 2026 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
