AD  - Akian College of Science and Engineering, Acopian Center for the Environment, American University of Armenia, Yerevan, Armenia
AB  - In recent years, online educational platforms have emerged as transformative tools in democratizing knowledge and enhancing accessibility to specialized education across sectors. The rapid evolution of digital technologies, combined with global challenges such as climate change and environmental degradation, has increased the demand for flexible, high-quality learning opportunities. Online platforms provide interactive, self-paced learning environments that transcend geographical barriers, fostering inclusivity and enabling learners to acquire new skills relevant to emerging fields. Their ability to deliver structured courses, tutorials, and resources at scale allows knowledge dissemination to be both timely and targeted, supporting lifelong learning and professional growth across academia, industry, and policy sectors. One critical area where such platforms playa transformative role is ocean literacy. By leveraging online platforms, education in ocean science can reach diverse audiences, including students, educators, professionals, and citizens. These platforms foster global awareness, inspire innovation, and empower individuals to take informed actions toward ocean conservation and sustainable development. Through structured educational pathways, they can bridge gaps in understanding, integrate scientific knowledge with practical tools, and engage stakeholders in co-creating solutions for ocean stewardship. In this context, the Iliad Academy is a pioneering online educational platform focusing on advancing ocean literacy and skill development in digital ocean technologies. Designed to support individuals and organizations engaged in ocean research, policy, and business, the Iliad Academy provides comprehensive resources, including documentation, tutorials, and structured courses. The platform offers specialized training on ocean modeling, ocean digitization tools, step-by-step guides on building digital twins of the ocean, virtual, high-fidelity representations of marine environments that integrate real-time data and predictive modeling. The platform is tailored to meet the needs of a diverse group of stakeholders, including researchers, technology developers, businesses, policymakers, and engaged citizens. By bridging the gap between cutting-edge science and practical application, The Iliad Academy plays a vital role in strengthening career pathways, enhancing business practices, and advancing policy goals related to ocean sustainability. The platform fosters interdisciplinary collaboration and knowledge-sharing, equipping stakeholders with the tools and expertise needed to address critical marine challenges such as climate change, biodiversity loss, and marine pollution. Its emphasis on digital ocean technologies, including digital twins, positions learners at the forefront of innovation, ensuring they remain competitive in an increasingly data-driven world. Moreover, as global priorities shift toward achieving the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), platforms like The Iliad Academy play an essential role in equipping stakeholders with the knowledge and tools to drive meaningful change for the future of our oceans.  © 2025 IEEE.
