AB  - This paper integrates studies on AI deployment in the Circular Economy through the lens of waste management, resource beneficiation, and product life cycle analysis. Examination of more than sixty studies in machine learning, digital twining, and IoT reveals that AI reduces wastage, boosts recycling coverage and accuracy, and enhances efficiency—up to 25% and 40% respectively. AI-based systems incorporating life cycle studies and real-time monitoring deliver closed-loop production and robust supply chains. However, the barriers exist in data quality and energy consumption by the AI systems and in the realms of ethics and scalability through gaps in policies and infrastructural support. The studies underscore the transformative power of AI while noting the imperative for overcoming socio-technical barriers to successful integration in circular economy transformations. Copyright © 2026, IGI Global Scientific Publishing. Copying or distributing in print or electronic forms without written permission of IGI Global Scientific Publishing is prohibited. Use of this chapter to train generative artificial intelligence (AI) technologies is expressly prohibited. The publisher reserves all rights to license its use for generative AI training and machine learning model development.
