AB  - To address the need for teaching, training, and assembly assistance in the assembly of complex industrial products, this research develops an engine assembly assistance system based on digital twin technology, overcoming the limitations of traditional assembly tools. Using the special-purpose vehicle engine as a case study, the system simulates assembly scenarios through digital twin technology and proposes an automated data collection and annotation algorithm. This algorithm generates synthetic datasets, effectively solving challenges related to data collection and the inefficiency of manual annotation. A deep learning model trained on these datasets recognizes assembly steps, while augmented reality technology provides real-time operational guidance. The system significantly enhances the interactivity of the assembly process, reduces learning costs and operational risks, and improves error tolerance and assembly efficiency. ©2025 IEEE.
