TI  - Exploring industry 5.0 in digital education: Concepts, applications, challenges, opportunities, and future directions - exploring Europe as an Education Hub
PY  - 2025
T2  - Digital Mentorship: Bridging AI-Human Divide in the Era of Industry 5.0
SP  - 165
EP  - 184
DO  - 10.1108/978-1-83662-252-920251010
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105014565063?origin=resultslist
AD  - Department of Management and Marketing, Jazan University, Jazan, Saudi Arabia
AB  - The swift progression of Industries 5.0 is revolutionizing education by prioritizing human-focused design and automated learning. Although education has traditionally advanced human progress by alleviating poverty and fostering equality, the contemporary system has substantial hurdles. This encompasses restricted customization, inadequate development of emotional intelligence, and an emphasis predominantly on Intelligence Quotient (IQ). The COVID-19 epidemic highlighted deficiencies in conventional schooling and standard assessment techniques, underscoring the necessity for more flexible and engaging educational paradigms. Industry 5.0 incorporates sophisticated technologies like artificial intelligence (AI), the Internet of Things (IoT), and digital twins, facilitating a tailored and human-centric training experience. This transition, referred to as Education 5.0, emphasizes the integration of human creativity with technology advancement, ensuring that learners cultivate emotional resilience, social competencies, and flexibility. Industry 5.0 promotes immersive and adaptable learning environments through the enhancement to work together between humans and robots. This assessment emphasizes the transformative potential of Industry 5.0 across many educational sectors, notably medical, vocational, as well as higher education. It underscores the necessity for modifications in curriculum, pedagogy, and assessment methodologies to correspond with the advancing requirements of Industry 5.0. These modifications will equip pupils for forthcoming problems, guaranteeing they obtain the essential abilities for a swiftly evolving workforce. Instruction 5.0 presents a holistic approach to learning, integrating technology progress with individualized instruction to cultivate well-rounded individuals prepared for career and societal progression. © 2025 by Umme Thayyiba Khatoon. All rights reserved.
