AB  - This study evaluates the current state of Measurement Science education through a comprehensive student survey and identifies areas for pedagogical and curricular improvements. Results show a significant lack of exposure to advanced topics such as Digital Twins, Industry 5.0, and AI, alongside limited application of active learning strategies. While traditional lectures remain widely accepted, students express a need for more practical, industry-relevant, and technology-integrated learning experiences. The paper proposes actionable recommendations to bridge the identified gaps and align education with contemporary industrial demands. © 2025 IEEE.
