AB  - In industrial process, fault detection and diagnosis (FDD) are critical to ensure system safety and reliability. However, the increasing complexity of operating environments and the growth in demand bring some challenges to FDD education. In this study, we analyze FDD methods based on multivariate statistical learning, deep learning, and the limitations on skill training. To bridge this gap, we propose a framework for AI-driven FDD education. The framework consists of a progressive three-tier teaching system built around theoretical learning, virtual simulation, and practical applications. On this foundation, a spiral competency development path, which includes FDD methods, digital twin verification, and physical system commissioning, is designed to enhance students' practical skills. The study showed that the above teaching model not only improved the understanding of industrial fault analysis, but also demonstrated efficiency in developing engineering practice and independent learning skills. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
