AB  - Numerical analysis of electromagnetic processes is essential for the design and optimization of electronic systems, assuring their reliable and safe operation. Computer Aided Design (CAD) and Computer-Aided Engineering (CAE) tools are indispensable and have become fundamental skills for all engineers. Consequently, engineering students should be intensively trained towards mastering the modern design tools in order equip them with the necessary competencies to address contemporary challenges in electronic system design and optimization. This paper presents the Design Workflow of a DC-DC Buck converter that aims to familiarize students with a range of CAD-CAE tools-specifically SolidWorks PCB, Ansys SIwave,-And to teach them how to compute parameters related to power distribution (DC) and signal transmission (AC). The emphasis is put on identifying potential issues such as voltage drops, high impedance, and Electromagnetic Integrity (EMI).  © 2025 IEEE.
