AB  - Artificial intelligence (AI) and the Internet of Things (IoT) are continuously enhancing various sectors, including smart healthcare, manufacturing, automobiles, and retail, in Industry 5.0. Digital twins (DTs) are virtual replicas of real-world entities created using AI. The Industrial 5.0 applications based on DTs are still in their early stages, even though DTs have been adopted and used successfully in the manufacturing and industrial sectors. The sharing of sensitive data is limited due to concerns surrounding privacy and trust. The combination of federated learning (FL) and DT has the potential to ensure the confidentiality and reliability of users' data. This chapter addresses how these two novel developments may be combined to promote the widespread usage of both innovations in real time, crucial circumstances, and the simple management of Industry 5.0 applications. Here, we propose a comprehensive overview of the numerous methods that involve FL models being used in DTs to assist efforts toward Industry 5.0. The chapter establishes several key issues as well as recommendations for stepping ahead to improve FL-DT collaboration for future deployments. © The Institution of Engineering and Technology and its licensors 2025.
