AB  - This research introduces an innovative approach to energy management by integrating auditing, modeling, and assessing energy infrastructure with digital twins and virtual reality technologies. The project focuses on a solar energy system installed in a rural ethno-educational school, demonstrating how sustainable energy solutions can be evaluated and optimized to address environmental challenges. At the heart of the project is an educational video game, developed through gamification techniques, which simulates a working solar energy system. Students are tasked with identifying key technological components to install and optimize energy efficiency, enhancing both technical and environmental literacy. This multi- and interdisciplinary approach not only improves learning outcomes but also provides a practical platform to study and refine energy management strategies. The game is linked to real-time data from IoT devices installed on the solar panels, ensuring accurate simulation results. Through continuous feedback, the prototype is refined and tested in controlled environments to assess how closely virtual data aligns with real-world energy performance. The project’s results have the potential to be incorporated into broader educational curricula, promoting the application of sustainable energy practices in rural and underserved communities. This initiative contributes to sustainable development goals (SDGs) while enhancing students’ understanding of renewable energy technologies in real-world settings. © 2026 selection and editorial matter, Hasan Saygin, Hasan Volkan Oral, Kaveh Dehghanian and Tevfik Denizhan Müftüoğlu, individual chapters, the contributors.
