AB  - The text discusses the latest research on essential issues and prospects surrounding the deployment of intelligent technologies, such as infrastructural needs, data privacy issues, and legislative considerations. It includes case studies of businesses using innovative technology for sustainable development. This book: • Investigates the relationship between intelligent technology and sustainable development, offering a thorough summary of how cutting-edge technological advancements might support an environmentally friendly future. • Discusses the role of using smart technologies in revolutionizing waste collection and recycling systems. • Explores ethical considerations in the implementation of smart technology and sustainability. • Highlights the latest innovations in smart transportation and digital twin technology. • Showcases the use of smart technologies in areas including energy management, transportation, waste management, water conservation, and healthcare. It is primarily written for senior undergraduates, graduate students, and academic researchers in fields including electrical engineering, electronics, communication engineering, computer science and engineering, information technology, civil engineering, and environmental engineering. © 2026 selection and editorial matter, Radhika Thapar, A. V Senthil Kumar, Fahad Alturise and Omar S. Saleh; individual chapters, the contributors.
