AB  - Machine learning (ML) technologies are being used more and more in the fast-developing field of additive manufacturing. The goal of this chapter is to examine the newest developments and uses of ML tools in additive manufacturing. ML algorithms can forecast temperature, pressure, humidity, and other variables that may have an impact on the quality of printed components. Additionally, ML has the ability to spot irregularities in production processes and raw materials, allowing for the early identification and avoidance of flaws. The chapter also considers difficulties like data privacy and security concerns as it evaluates the benefits and drawbacks of ML indulgences in manufacturing, including greater quality control, less waste, and higher productivity. Overall, this chapter emphasizes the potential of machine learning (ML) in additive manufacturing and its influence on the sector, including the invention of novel materials, the improvement of the printing process, and new applications. Last, but not least, it describes the difficulties and potential directions of ML-based additive manufacturing, offering insights into the new patterns and chances in this fascinating area. © 2025 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
