AB  - The intersection of Generative Artificial Intelligence and Digital Twins presents a paradigm shift in personalised data-driven learning ecosystems. This qualitative synthesis focuses on the ways in which the combination of GenAI and DTs transforms the human experience in education, and ethical governance. The paper will discuss the mediation of trust, autonomy, and pedagogical relationships by hybrid AI-DT systems. The results indicate that there is an ongoing conflict between customisation and surveillance, effectiveness and reliance, and automation and judgement. The long-term success of these systems depends on socio-technical design frameworks that anticipate transparency, fairness, and human controls. This article provides a qualitative basis to comprehend how GenAI-DT convergence reformulates the instructor-learner-technology triad and suggests potential ways of responsible innovation of educational practice. Copyright © 2026, IGI Global Scientific Publishing.
