AB  - In this study, we introduce an educational course for training the semiconductor device. The course is divided into two primary sections: a virtual space created through Digital-Twin and Solid-edge for 3D reverse engineering. We made the semiconductor device in the Digital Twin environment using Unity. This device can be inspected from various perspectives. Using the mock-up and model inside the Digital-Twin as reference, we can reverse engineer the device using Solid-edge. Once the reverse engineering process is completed, we can redesign or resize the device for testing experiments. Finally, the reverse-engineered device can be 3D-printed to verify the results. Through these processes, we aim to provide students with hands-on experience and enhance their understanding of equipment operation and design.  © 2024 IEEE.
