AB  - The industrial sector increasingly demands higher accuracy and real-time capabilities in heat exchanger data modeling. This study constructs a physics-informed deep residual network model, achieving high-precision prediction of finned tube heat exchanger performance through dedicated networks for heat transfer and pressure drop estimation. The study employs a cascaded network structure optimization method to enhance prediction accuracy and utilizes transfer learning technology to facilitate model adaptation for practical engineering applications. This approach significantly improves the computational efficiency of heat exchanger digital twins, offering new insights for performance optimization in complex refrigeration and air-conditioning systems. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
