AB  - Aiming at the low utilization rate of equipment and space in the process of logistics storage, a method of real-time monitoring of equipment and cargo transportation storage in the process of production by using digital twin technology is proposed. Firstly, the grid model simplification method based on Quadric Error Metrics (QEM) is used to construct the virtual model, which improves the computing power of the model while retaining the geometric features of the model. After that, the communication between PLC and Unity3d was realized through S7.net protocol, and the virtual and real linkage technology of digital twin was implemented. Finally, taking stacker, crane, shelf, AGV and other equipment as an example, the digital management and control of the production process is realized, and the virtual and real linkage technology is adopted to realize the virtual control and real-time monitoring of the industrial production site. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
