AB  - The present logistics and supply chain workforce needs staff members who can perform operational tasks while possessing digital technology skills. The current warehouse operation training methods encounter multiple barriers because they require expensive equipment and present safety hazards and insufficient adaptable training spaces. The authors present a Smart Warehouse Logistics Virtual Reality (VR) Simulator, which they developed to enhance practical learning experiences for warehouse operation training. The system duplicates complete logistics operations from receiving to shipping through sorting and error resolution in a physics-based 3D environment built with the Meta Quest 3 VR headset and Unity Engine and C# programming. The system enables learners to practice realistic warehouse operations through its combination of automated conveyor and sorting logic and forklift dynamics and error-handling mechanisms. The system architecture contains three separate layers (Input and Logic Core and Output) which allows for expansion and future connection to Industry 4.0 systems and digital twin platforms. The evaluation study employed a mixed-methods research design to evaluate system usability and student learning outcomes through a study with 32 undergraduate logistics students. The usability assessment through SUS reached 86.2, while participants demonstrated 48.7% better knowledge retention and their process errors decreased by 63.6%. The research participants gave feedback which showed their work engagement improved while they achieved better safety standards and operational performance. © 2026 IEEE.
