AB  - This work aims to explore the integration of Mixed Reality (MR), Digital Twin (DT), and Artificial Intelligence (AI) technologies to create innovative and accessible training solutions to support Borderline Intellectual Functioning (BIF) people. Its primary focus is to make the process of learning to operate and work with workplace devices more intuitive, engaging, and adaptable to people with learning difficulties. Through realistic MR simulations, AI-driven personalization, and DT-enabled real-time guidance, it seeks to enhance current practices in occupational training. In this paper we present the envisioned scenarios for the proposed training artifacts, the first prototypes implemented and outline the steps of a development process that explores how AI technologies can streamline their creation. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
