AB  - Universal scholars as they once existed no longer exist today; our world is too complex and the tasks that need to be solved by specialists with in-depth expertise are too individual. This also applies to automation technology. Increasingly extensive knowledge is required for system design and programming, and rapid developments make conventional training difficult. A new learning method with virtual content, in which digital plant twins can be used to set up and program even self-created plants, allows for flexible learning in line with the latest state of the art. Another advantage is that costly mechanical training models are no longer necessary and interdisciplinary training content becomes possible. © 2025 Walter de Gruyter GmbH, Berlin/Boston, Germany.
