AB  - The research explores the integration of Artificial Intelligence (AI), Machine Learning (ML), and Digital Twin technologies within the textile industry to facilitate the transition from traditional manufacturing practices to smart, data-driven systems under the Industry 4.0 paradigm. Leveraging over three decades of industrial expertise in textile engineering combined with advanced knowledge of AI and ML, we present a comprehensive framework for modernizing textile operations. Applications include yarn quality parameters prediction, real-time Knitting machine/Loom efficiency monitoring, Sentiment analysis through customer review/ feedback data, prediction of mixing category required for specific yarn quality parameters, predictive maintenance and computer-vision based defect detection. This study highlights the role of AI-driven digital twins in simulating, analyzing, and optimizing textile processes, offering a roadmap for achieving higher efficiency, flexibility, and sustainability in textile production.  © 2025 IEEE.
