AD  - COER University, Uttarakhand, Roorkee, India
AB  - Reducing wastage is a critical challenge faced by humans and industries worldwide. Digital twin technology and machine learning algorithms offer a powerful solution for optimizing waste management processes and improving resource utilization. This review paper provides a comprehensive analysis of the applications, methodologies, and benefits of integrating digital twin technology and machine learning algorithms in waste management. By creating a virtual replica of the various products and leveraging machine learning algorithms to examine data and improve processes, organizations can achieve efficient methods to increase product durability and cost savings. The paper explores various aspects of product monitoring, prediction, and optimization, and discusses the challenges, potential solutions, and future directions for leveraging digital twin technology and machine learning in waste reduction.  © 2023 IEEE.
