AB  - Considering the smart manufacturing context and the numerous opportunities to transform businesses, manufacturing companies are urging for options to improve current workforce skills by proper training in these new industrial technologies, enabling the desired digital transformation in shop-floor processes. On the other hand, together with the training is the need for technical consulting by leveraging disruptive scientific research results in real-world industrial applications. The Self-Made Program aims to deliver innovative training courses and tailored technical consulting to manufacturing companies. This will enable the exploitation of educational assets in topics such as Digitalization, Cyber-Physical Systems and the IEC 61499 standard. Finally, the program enables the experimentation and deployment of disruptive technologies in a Teaching and Learning Factory and in real-world environments to support the digital transformation of such companies. © 2023, The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG.
