AB  - Experimental teaching refers to an organizational form of practical teaching in which students observe, measure and analyze research objects under the guidance of teachers, using instruments and equipment, and under the condition of human control, so as to obtain knowledge and develop ability. It has been widely used in basic courses and professional courses in Colleges and universities. Its purpose is not only to verify book knowledge, but also to cultivate students’ ability to correctly use instruments and equipment, test, adjust, analyze, synthesize, design experimental schemes, and prepare experimental reports. In view of a series of problems such as insufficient investment of experimental equipment and no hardware involved in virtual simulation in PLC experimental teaching, this paper discusses the basic idea and related problems of developing experimental teaching platform by using digital twin technology. Integrate the OBE education concept into the teaching, define the ability training objectives, establish the experimental course system, carry out various teaching reforms relying on the digital twin technology, and complete the teaching evaluation through the student ability training effect experiment, providing a new idea for the PLC Course Experimental Teaching Reform and the application of the digital twin technology in the teaching. © 2023, The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG.
