AB  - With the rapid development of building information modeling and deep learning technology, as well as people's increasing demand for virtual reality and intelligent construction projects, time-consuming and inefficient manual building modeling methods are far from meeting engineering needs. Plane detection is also gradually unable to meet the needs of building earthquake resistance. This paper proposes a generation and detection technique for intelligent construction projects based on digital twins and deep learning. First, using digital twin technology, the building plane is obtained through the Boolean intersection operation between geometric objects, and then the main body, external working conditions, environment and other entities are faithfully reproduced in the building information model; Contour; Finally, based on the Boltzmann machine of deep learning, the contour outside the building plane is input into the trained anomaly detection neural network algorithm model, and the recognition result is fed back. The experimental results show that the algorithm model has greatly improved the recognition rate of the abnormal detection of concave-convex irregular building plans, and is more in line with the actual needs of intelligent building construction.  © 2023 IEEE.
