AB  - Rapidly increasing level of digitalization in all levels of society create pressure for software engineering education about capacity to apply also higher abstraction level physics or mathematics in selected application areas. In this study a simple simulation solution was implemented with standard software tools (Python and open-source libraries) to create and test example of an approach to tackle the challenges about combining simple software and abstraction levels of mathematics or physics. The results illustrate that it is possible to implement higher level ideas by simple software implementations like shown in this study. The findings and reflections of this study may be useful in education or application development in software engineering in fields of artificial intelligence, collaborative robotics, or digital twins.  © 2022 IEEE.
