AB  - Current lecture methods at educational institutions are still performed analogously and mostly try to query knowledge from the students. Moreover, the field of digital skills, which is uncared of, gets increasingly crucial for today’s work life. Practical laboratory courses were introduced to counteract the analog-fashioned and theoretical lecture methods. The crux in these practical laboratories is that the interconnection between theoretical knowledge and practical application is entirely missing. Moreover, these practical courses have the disadvantage that they are limited locally and temporally. This full paper tackles the above mentioned problems by mitigating the gap between knowledge and practical laboratory by visualizing otherwise unseen information with digital methods. At first, a digital twin of a laboratory experiment, here an extraction plant, has been transferred to a virtual reality laboratory (VR-Lab) using Unreal Engine. This twin allows the operation of the extraction plant and extracting pre-captured experimental data. The second part deals with efficient methods of data evaluation using advanced artificial intelligence (AI) in Google Colabs. It is a more student-centered and sustainable, in terms of utilized resources, approach compared to conventional laboratory courses. © 2023, The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG.
